  <h2>Wait, tell me the future!</h2>

  <p>Oh, there'll be OAuth, a slowly evolving registry protocol, and lots of ways to plug your own sites and apps into the Userpedia API.</p>

  <p>For me, I'm going to use the Userpedia to build a better-than-email protocol over HTTP. I've already got a laundry list of revolutionary features that people love. Now, will my federated starmail system actually gain adoption? I've got no clue. But, what I do know is that without the foundation of something like the Userpedia, my starmail project would never be able to get off the ground.</p>

  <p>Likewise, the Userpedia has the chance to open up innovation across the net for new projects. And so while I know that the future of the Userpedia and starnames will be bright, I don't know what exactly it will hold. After all, the future should be yours, and who knows what you'll build.</p>

